  "prompt": "How can I add more topics here in Quora?",
  "response": "To add more topics to a question or answer on Quora, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Create a Question or Answer:** If you are posting a new question or providing an answer to an existing one, start by typing it in the appropriate section.\n\n2. **Adding Topics:**\n   - When you type your question, you will see an option to add topics. Look for the \u201cAdd topics\u201d section usually found on the right side of the question box.\n   - If you're answering a question, the topic needs to be relevant to the content of your answer.\n\n3. **Search for Topics:** Start typing the name of the topic you want to add. Quora will suggest existing topics based on your input. You can select from the suggestions or create a new topic if it doesn't already exist.\n\n4. **Creating a New Topic:** If the topic you want to add does not exist, when you start typing, you might see an option to create a new topic. Click on it, and you can provide the name of the new topic.\n\n5. **Save Changes:** Once you have added the desired topics, make sure to save or submit your question or answer.\n\nRemember, topics should be relevant and useful to the Quora community, so ensure that the topics you add align with the content you are posting.",
